# Git remote (Secret Millionaire Society)

This project pushes to **https://github.com/neoai2020/secretmillionaire**.

When the user says **push** (or asks to push changes):

1. Use `origin` → `https://github.com/neoai2020/secretmillionaire.git`
2. Only push when explicitly requested — do not push proactively after commits
3. Use `git push -u origin HEAD` on first push for a new branch; otherwise `git push origin <branch>`
4. Never force-push to `main`/`master` unless the user explicitly asks

Repository is currently empty on GitHub; first push may need an initial commit on the default branch.
